  "english": [
    "However, the Gemara states: <b>And</b> the <b><i>halakha</i></b> is <b>not in accordance with</b> that opinion. Instead, the <i>halakha</i> is in accordance with the opinion of Shmuel.",
    "The Gemara relates: <b>Ulla happened</b> to come <b>to Pumbedita. Rav Yehuda said to his son, Rav Yitzḥak: Go</b> and <b>bring him a basket of fruit</b> as a gift, <b>and</b> while you are there, <b>observe how he recites <i>havdala</i>.</b> Rav Yitzḥak himself <b>did not go.</b> In his place, <b>he sent to him Abaye,</b> who was a young student at the time. <b>When Abaye came</b> back, Rav Yitzḥak <b>said to him: How did</b> Ulla <b>recite</b> the blessing of <i>havdala</i>? Abaye <b>said to him</b> that Ulla <b>said: Blessed is He Who distinguishes between sacred and profane, but</b> he did <b>not</b> say anything <b>further.</b>",
    "Rav Yitzḥak <b>came before his father,</b> Rav Yehuda, who <b>said to him: How did</b> Ulla <b>recite</b> <i>havdala</i>? <b>He said to him: I</b> myself <b>did not go.</b> Instead, <b>I sent Abaye, who said to me</b> that Ulla recited: <b>Who distinguishes between sacred and profane.</b> Rav Yehuda grew angry and <b>said to him: The Master’s haughtiness and the Master’s pride caused the Master</b> to act in a way that ensured <b>that</b> the <b><i>halakha</i> will not be said in his name.</b> In other words, had you gone yourself, this <i>halakha</i> would have been attributed to you, but due to your haughtiness and pride, it will be transmitted in the name of Abaye.",
    "The Gemara <b>raises an objection</b> to Ulla’s practice from a <i>baraita</i>: With regard to <b>all blessings,</b> one <b>begins</b> their recitation <b>with: Blessed, and concludes</b> reciting <b>them with: Blessed, except for blessings over mitzvot, blessings over fruit, a blessing that is juxtaposed to another</b> blessing in the order of prayer, e.g., during the <i>Amida</i> prayer, <b>and the final blessing after <i>Shema</i>.</b>",
    "The <i>baraita</i> elaborates: These blessings are different, <b>as some of them begin with: Blessed, and do not conclude with: Blessed,</b> e.g., blessings over mitzvot and before eating, <b>and some of them conclude with: Blessed, and do not begin with: Blessed,</b> such as a blessing that is juxtaposed to another blessing. <b>And</b> the blessing: <b>He Who is good and does good,</b> is exceptional, as it is a blessing that is juxtaposed to another blessing, and yet it <b>begins with: Blessed, and does not conclude with: Blessed.</b>"
  ],
  "gemara": [
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "<span class=\"sentence\" id=\"0\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>וְלֵית הִלְכְתָא כְּווֹתֵיהּ. <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"1\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>עוּלָּא אִיקְּלַע",
      "segment_ids": [
        0,
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "לְפוּמְבְּדִיתָא, אֲמַר לֵיהּ רַב יְהוּדָה לְרַב יִצְחָק",
      "segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "בְּרֵיהּ: זִיל אַמְטִי לֵיהּ כַּלְכַּלָּה דְפֵירֵי, וַחֲזִי הֵיכִי",
      "segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "אַבְדֵּיל. לָא אֲזַל, שַׁדַּר לֵיהּ לְאַבָּיֵי. כִּי אֲתָא",
      "segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "אַבָּיֵי, אֲמַר לֵיהּ: הֵיכִי אָמַר? אֲמַר לֵיהּ: ״בָּרוּךְ הַמַּבְדִּיל בֵּין",
      "segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "קוֹדֶשׁ לְחוֹל״ אָמַר, וְתוּ לָא. <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"2\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>אֲתָא לְקַמֵּיהּ דַּאֲבוּהּ, אֲמַר",
      "segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "לֵיהּ: הֵיכִי אָמַר? אֲמַר לֵיהּ: אֲנָא לָא אֲזַלִי, אֲנָא",
      "segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "שַׁדְּרִיתֵיהּ לְאַבָּיֵי, וַאֲמַר לִי ״הַמַּבְדִּיל בֵּין קוֹדֶשׁ",
      "segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "לְחוֹל״. אֲמַר לֵיהּ: רַבְרְבָנוּתֵיהּ דְּמָר, וּסְרָרוּתֵיהּ דְּמָר,",
      "segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "גְּרַמָא לֵיהּ לְמָר דְּלָא תֵּימָא שְׁמַעְתֵּיהּ מִפּוּמֵּיהּ.",
      "segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "<span class=\"sentence\" id=\"3\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>מֵיתִיבִי: כׇּל הַבְּרָכוֹת כּוּלָּן פּוֹתֵחַ בְּבָרוּךְ",
      "segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "וְחוֹתֵם בָּהֶן בְּבָרוּךְ, חוּץ מִבִּרְכַּת מִצְוֹת וּבִרְכַּת",
      "segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "הַפֵּירוֹת וּבְרָכָה הַסְּמוּכָה לַחֲבֶירְתָּהּ וּבְרָכָה",
      "segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "אַחֲרוֹנָה שֶׁבִּקְרִיַּת שְׁמַע, <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"4\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>שֶׁיֵּשׁ מֵהֶן פּוֹתֵחַ",
      "segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "(בָּהֶן) בְּבָרוּךְ וְאֵין חוֹתֵם בְּבָרוּךְ, וְיֵשׁ מֵהֶן",
      "segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "שֶׁחוֹתֵם בְּבָרוּךְ וְאֵין פּוֹתֵחַ בְּבָרוּךְ. וְ״הַטּוֹב",
      "segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "וְהַמֵּטִיב״ פּוֹתֵחַ בְּבָרוּךְ וְאֵינוֹ חוֹתֵם בְּבָרוּךְ.",
      "segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    }
  ],
  "rashi": [
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b>הַמַּבְדִּיל בֵּין קוֹדֶשׁ לְחוֹל״</b> ותו לא אמר בה שאר הבדלות ולא חתם בה:",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 104b:2:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b><span class=\"dh-divergent\">היא</span> גְּרַמָא לֵיהּ לְמָר</b> שלא הלכת אתה בעצמך: <b>וברכת</b> <b>המצות.</b> כגון",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 104b:3:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "להתעטף בציצית ועל נטילת לולב: <b>וּבְרָכָה הַסְּמוּכָה <span class=\"dh-divergent\">לחברתה</span></b> כגון",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 104b:4:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "אותם של שמונה עשרה: <b>וּבְרָכָה אַחֲרוֹנָה שֶׁבִּקְרִיַּת שְׁמַע.</b> אע\"פ שאין",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 104b:4:3",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "ברכה אחרת למעלה הימנה שהתחיל",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 104b:4:3",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "בה בברוך: <b><span class=\"dh-divergent\">יש</span> מֵהֶן.</b> מאלו שהזכרנו",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 104b:5:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "שפותח בהן בברוך ואינו חותם",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 104b:5:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "בברוך כגון ברכת פירות ומצות:",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 104b:5:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b>וְיֵשׁ מֵהֶן שֶׁחוֹתֵם <span class=\"dh-divergent\">ואינו</span> פּוֹתֵחַ.</b> כגון",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 104b:5:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "ברכה הסמוכה לחבירתה שהרי",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 104b:5:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "פוטרתה ראשונה שנפתחה בברוך:",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 104b:5:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b><span class=\"dh-divergent\">הטוב</span> וְהַמֵּטִיב״.</b> אף על גב דסמוכה",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 104b:5:3",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "לחבירתה שהרי התחיל בברכת",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 104b:5:3",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
